modules.description: This module offers date arithmetic, comparison, and ISO8601 formatting operations, enabling precise manipulation of `date` values through additions like period offsets or day counts. It handles `period` values by decomposing intervals into exact days or structured (years, months, days) units, with strict error handling for incompatible units. Common applications include financial calculations requiring exact day counts and scheduling systems needing structured time intervals.

This module performs date arithmetic, comparison, and ISO8601 formatting on `date` values, supporting operations like adding periods or day counts. It works with `date` and `period` types, decomposing intervals into exact days or structured (years, months, days) units. It is used in financial calculations for precise day counting and in scheduling systems for structured time interval management.
